{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"057fd1bd-fe63-4f2b-8963-4d20c967af08","content":"On macOS, the OS automatically generates crash reports:\n\n1. **Crash reports** are saved to:\n   - `~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/` (user apps)\n   - `/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/` (system-wide)\n\n   Look for `.ips` files matching your process name.\n\n2. **Core dumps** — macOS disables them by default. To enable:\n   ```bash\n   ulimit -c unlimited\n   ```\n   Cores are written to `/cores/core.<pid>`.\n\n3. **Console.app** — You can also browse crash reports in the built-in Console app under **Crash Reports**.\n\nFor NativeAOT specifically, the `.ips` crash log will contain the native backtrace with function addresses. If you built with debug symbols, you can symbolicate the frames using `atos` or `llvm-symbolizer`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"c6e0861f-eb85-4e7d-b69d-06690636981d","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about finding crash dumps/reports for a NativeAOT .NET app on macOS, without createdump. This is a knowledge question - I don't need to search code or run commands. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":283,"requestId":"6806:270DE0:185F51A:1B67D81:69FD41DA"},"id":"764441a9-828b-435d-ad12-007f5ad5743d","timestamp":"2026-05-08T01:52:35.507Z","parentId":"30014835-296a-4d16-95d1-511262e3cc55"}
